NAME

      gcloud beta deployment-manager operations - commands for Deployment
         Manager V2 operations

SYNOPSIS

      gcloud beta deployment-manager operations COMMAND [GLOBAL-FLAG ...]

DESCRIPTION

      (BETA) Commands to list, examine, and wait for long-running operations.

GLOBAL FLAGS

      Run $ gcloud help for a description of flags available to all commands.

COMMANDS

      COMMAND is one of the following:

      describe

         (BETA) Provide information about an operation.

      list

         (BETA) List operations in a project.

      wait

         (BETA) Wait for all operations specified to complete before returning.

EXAMPLES

      To view the details of an operation, run:

        $ gcloud beta deployment-manager operations describe operation-name

      To see the list of all operations, run:

        $ gcloud beta deployment-manager operations list

      To wait for an operation to complete, run:

        $ gcloud beta deployment-manager operations wait operation-name

NOTES

      This command is in the Google Cloud SDK gcloud component. See installing
      components if it is not installed.

      This command is currently in BETA and may change without notice.

